org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.things

Class VeluxProductState

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.things.VeluxProductState

  • @NonNullByDefault
public class VeluxProductState
extends java.lang.Object
    Velux product characteristics: Product State.

    Combined set of information which describes a current state of a single Velux product.

    Methods in handle this type of information:
    • VeluxProductState(VeluxProductReference, int, int) to create a new product state.
    • getActuator() to retrieve the number representing this actuator/product.
    • getProductReference() to retrieve reference to a product.
    • getState() to retrieve the current product state.
    • getStateAsInt() to retrieve the current product state.
    • toString() to retrieve a human-readable description of the product state.
    Author:
    Guenther Schreiner - initial contribution.
